
⸻

FG-421 — Cert Amicus “One-Screen” Card
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Each amicus should fit on one screen: QP • Topic • Relief.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Box 1 = Question Presented; Box 2 = Amicus topic (policy/data/split); Box 3 = Relief (adopts ladder). Hash at footer.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a one-screen amicus card for your case.
	•	✅ Model Response: “QP: Must courts reach findings? Topic: Policy harms of skipped review. Relief: adopt grant/GVR/hold.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Amici persuade when tight.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A palm card split into three neat boxes.

⸻

FG-422 — Cert Amicus Service Log (Who • When • Proof)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: SCOTUS demands service proof for amici.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Log: Amicus name • Served on • Date • Proof (affidavit); post as appendix tab; hash PDF.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 5-row amicus service log.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Amicus A—served 09/10—Affidavit filed 09/12 (Tab 6).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Proof beats disputes.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A checklist with green checks per amicus row.

⸻

FG-423 — Cert Pool “Ready Box” (QP • Split • Relief)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Draft your petition so it drops cleanly into a pool memo.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Front page box: QP (≤15 words), Split map (2–3 rows), Relief menu. Label “Ready Box.”
	•	📝 Assignment: Add a Ready Box to your petition draft.
	•	✅ Model Response: “QP: Must courts reach findings? Split: 2d—no; 9th—yes. Relief: grant/GVR/hold.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Clerk-ready = credibility.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A shaded sidebar titled “Ready Box.”

⸻

FG-424 — Cert Appendix Neutralization (Titles • Capture • Hash)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Keep appendix neutral—no argument in titles.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Titles: “Order, 09/01,” not “Erroneous Order”; each tab has capture/hash; sealed tabs in S-index.
	•	📝 Assignment: Rewrite 3 appendix titles into neutral form.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Tab 2 — Opinion (09/01) — SHA-256 ….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Neutrality travels.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Binder tabs with calm, plain labels.

⸻

FG-425 — Cert Supplemental Brief (≤15 Pages, Pin-First)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Keep cert supplements short and pin-driven.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: ≤15 pages; start with reason (new case/fact); add 2 pins; propose relief ladder; hash.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 2-page skeleton for a supplemental brief.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Reason: Doe (2025) deepens split. Pin: ‘Not reached’ (Dkt 18:2). Relief: grant/GVR/hold.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Supplements update, not repeat.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A slim update card clipped to the petition.

⸻

FG-426 — Cert Amicus Duplication Certification
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Show amici are not duplicating arguments.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Statement: “Amicus A covers split; Amicus B covers equities; both adopt relief text.” File with amici.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a duplication certification for 2 amici.
	•	✅ Model Response: “A covers split; B covers equities; both adopt petition relief; no duplication.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Coordination breeds credibility.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two arrows into one relief tile.

⸻

FG-427 — Cert OA Bench Trio (QP • Pins • Relief)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Prepare three cards: QP card, Pin card, Relief card.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: QP card = ≤15 words; Pin card = 2 record cites; Relief card = ladder; hash all three.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft and print your bench trio.
	•	✅ Model Response: “QP: Must courts reach findings? Pin: Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2. Relief: grant/GVR/hold.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Trios survive pressure.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Three small palm cards with hash tag footer.

⸻

FG-428 — Cert Amicus Bank Release Note
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Amici must log their release too.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: 100-word note: date filed, SHA-256, topic, relief adopted. Post to microsite.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a release note for one amicus.
	•	✅ Model Response: “09/12—Amicus on policy filed (sha …). Relief adopted: grant/GVR/hold. Next: reply due 09/20.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Logs earn trust.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A press card with fingerprint footer.

⸻

FG-429 — Cert Mandate Hold Motion (Post-Grant)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: After grant, seek a mandate hold below.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Motion: identify SCOTUS grant; cite Rule 41(d)(2); ask for hold pending decision; propose 21d status.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-line hold motion for the lower court.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Grant of cert 09/15; Rule 41(d)(2); ask: hold mandate; status 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Post-grant, pause the machinery.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A gavel with a pause icon.

⸻

FG-430 — Cert Final Closeout Kit
	•	⚖️ Core Message: End SCOTUS phase with a ZIP release + README.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Include: Petition.pdf, Appendix.pdf, Amicus briefs, Reply.pdf, CHECKSUMS.txt, ReleaseNote.md. Post mirrors; hash.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build the ZIP and draft a 120-word release note.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Release v3—Cert closeout kit posted: Petition (sha …), Appendix (sha …), Amici (sha …). Mirrors aligned.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Closure = institutional memory.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A ribboned ZIP folder with four doc icons and a fingerprint.
